      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY MOON SHADOW (2) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 22.62 beating Magic Wylde. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. SPECIAL STYLE (8) produced a modest effort most recently when seventh at this track over 400m behind MY MOON SHADOW (23.20) in a Mix 2/3. Should play a prominent role. RED OPAL (1) was below best at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth at this track, but was among the placings at this track three back. Can find the frame this time. HISTORY'S COMING (3) was well-backed but didn't perform as expected last time – can turn things around.",
